\subsection{Pre-training Strategy}

Tab.~\ref{tab:ablation_pretrain} compares ImageNet-pretrained initialisation with training from scratch. Pre-training yields a 4.4$\times$ higher mIoU (0.178 vs.\ 0.041), the largest single-factor improvement across all five ablations. The from-scratch model barely exceeds chance-level performance after 25 epochs, achieving only 62.7\% pixel accuracy. This underscores the critical importance of transfer learning when labelled segmentation data is scarce: the low-level and mid-level features learned on ImageNet provide a strong initialisation that dramatically accelerates convergence on downstream tasks.

